import { useState, useCallback, useEffect, useRef } from 'react'
 
useState → Stores component state (like length, Password, checkboxes).
useCallback → Memoizes functions to avoid recreating them on every render (optimization).
useEffect → Runs side-effects (like generating a password when dependencies change).
useRef → Gets direct reference to a DOM element (here, the input box).

_______________________________________________________________________________________________________

const [length, setLength] = useState(10)
const [numberAllowed, setNumberAllowed] = useState(false)
const [characterAllowed, setCharacterAllowed] = useState(false)
const [Password, setPassword] = useState('')

length → Password length slider. Default: 10.
numberAllowed → Include numbers (0–9) in password? Default: false.
characterAllowed → Include special characters? Default: false.
Password → Stores the generated password. Default: empty.

_______________________________________________________________________________________________________

const passwordRef = useRef(null)
Points to the password input box so we can select and copy text programmatically

___________________________________________________________________

const passwordGenerator = useCallback(() => {
    let pass = ""      // Store generated password
    let str = "ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz"  // Base letters

    if(numberAllowed) str += "0123456789"      // Add numbers if allowed
    if(characterAllowed) str += "!@#$%^&*()_+" // Add symbols if allowed

    for (let i = 1; i <= length; i++) {
        let char = Math.floor(Math.random() * str.length + 1)
        pass += str.charAt(char)
    }

    setPassword(pass)
}, [length, numberAllowed, characterAllowed, setPassword])

Explanation:

1. useCallback → Prevents function recreation unless dependencies change.
2. Builds a string str of possible characters.
3. Loops length times, picks a random char from str.
4. Stores final password in Password state.
___________________________________________________________________

const copyPasswordToClipboard = useCallback(() => {
    passwordRef.current?.select()                  // Select input content
    passwordRef.current?.setSelectionRange(0, 9999) // Ensure full selection
    window.navigator.clipboard.writeText(Password) // Copy to clipboard
}, [Password])

Copies current password to clipboard.
Memoized with useCallback for optimization.
Uses passwordRef to access input DOM element directly.
___________________________________________________________________

useEffect to Auto-generate Password:

    useEffect(() => {
    passwordGenerator()
}, [length, numberAllowed, characterAllowed, passwordGenerator])

Runs once on mount and whenever dependencies change (length, numberAllowed, characterAllowed).
Ensures password is updated automatically when slider or checkboxes change.
___________________________________________________________________

UI Explanation : 

1. Main Container
    <div className='text-orange-600 bg-gray-800 px-4 py-3 mx-auto my-10 rounded-lg shadow-md max-w-md w-full'>
  
Purpose: Wraps the entire password generator app.
Classes Explained:

text-orange-600 → Default text color for inner text (some labels inherit this).
bg-gray-800 → Dark gray background for the card.
px-4 py-3 → Padding inside the container (horizontal & vertical).
mx-auto my-10 → Center horizontally, margin top/bottom for spacing.
rounded-lg → Rounded corners for a smooth card look.
shadow-md → Drop shadow for depth effect.
max-w-md w-full → Card has max width and is responsive.

Visual Effect: This creates a centered, card-like container with padding, rounded corners, and shadow — makes it feel like a “panel” floating on the page.

2. TITLE
    <h1 className='text-white text-center m-5'>password generator</h1>

Purpose: Displays the app title.
Classes Explained:
text-white → White font color to contrast with dark background.
text-center → Center aligns text.
m-5 → Margin on all sides for spacing.
Visual Effect: A clean, centered title at the top of the card.

3. Password Display Box

    <div className='flex shadow rounded-lg overflow-hidden mb-4'>
    <input
        type="text"
        value={Password}
        className='outline-none w-full py-1 px-3'
        placeholder='Your Password'
        readOnly
        ref={passwordRef}
    />
    <button
        onClick={copyPasswordToClipboard}
        className='text-green-600 bg-gray-600 px-3 py-0.5'
    >
        copy
    </button>
</div>


Purpose: Shows the generated password and a button to copy it.

Outer Div Classes:
flex → Arrange input and button side by side.
shadow → Adds a subtle depth effect.
rounded-lg → Smooth corners.
overflow-hidden → Ensures rounded corners are respected by children.
mb-4 → Margin below the box for spacing.

Input Box Classes:
outline-none → Removes default browser outline.
w-full → Takes all remaining horizontal space.
py-1 px-3 → Padding inside input.
readOnly → User cannot type manually.

Button Classes:
text-green-600 → Green text for “copy” to indicate action.
bg-gray-600 → Button background color.
px-3 py-0.5 → Small padding for compact button.

Visual Effect: Looks like a single rounded box with input and a small action button on the right — similar to a modern form field with action.


4. Controls Container:

        <div className='flex text-sm gap-x-2'>
Purpose: Wraps the slider and checkboxes in one row.

Classes:

flex → Children arranged horizontally.
text-sm → Small text for labels.
gap-x-2 → Horizontal spacing between children.

Visual Effect: Controls are evenly spaced in a horizontal row.


5. Slider (Password Length)
        <div className='flex items-center gap-x-1'>
    <input 
        type="range"
        value={length}
        min={10}
        max={100}
        className='cursor-pointer'
        onChange={(e) => {setLength(e.target.value)}}
    />
    <label>length: {length}</label>
</div>

Purpose: Adjust password length dynamically.
Outer Div: Flex layout for slider + label.

Classes:
flex items-center → Aligns slider and label vertically.
gap-x-1 → Small spacing between slider and label.

Slider Input:
type="range" → HTML slider element.
cursor-pointer → Shows pointer cursor on hover.

Label: Shows the current password length.

Visual Effect: Slider + label appears as a single line, interactive for adjusting length.


6. Checkbox Options:
        <div className='flex items-center gap-x-1'>
    <input type="checkbox" ... />
    <label htmlFor='number'>Numbers</label>
</div>

Purpose: Allow users to toggle inclusion of numbers or special characters.

Outer Div Classes:
flex items-center → Checkbox + label aligned in one row.
gap-x-1 → Small spacing between checkbox and label.

Checkbox: Standard input. onChange toggles the respective state.

Label: Explains what the checkbox does.

Visual Effect: Simple, clean toggle options aligned neatly.

_______________________________________________________________________________________________________

7. Overall Visual Flow

Card container → Centered panel with padding and shadow.
Title → Centered, stands out.
Password display + copy button → Looks like a single interactive field.
Slider for length → Intuitive way to change password size.
Checkboxes → Toggle options without clutter.

Result:
A compact, modern, and readable UI for password generation, easy to use, visually organized, and responsive.